k9.name: Frida
k9.bio: Frida was a service dog for Dolores del Río. She was a Labrador Retriever, and was trained to help Dolores with her blindness. She was also trained to help Dolores with her depression. Frida was a very important part of Dolores' life, and she was with her for 49 years.
k9.image-alt: Frida, a Labrador Retriever, sitting on a couch with Dolores del Río
k9.handlerBio: Dolores del Río was a Mexican actress and singer. She was one of the most famous Latin American actresses of the 1920s and 1930s. She was also a singer, and was known as the 'Mexican Songbird'.
